quran[98]{c,v,t}:
  19,1,K H Y EN S/C
  19,2,Your Lord`s mercy mention (on) His worshipper/slave Zachary/Zacharias
  19,3,When he called/cried (to) his Lord a hidden/secret call/cry
  19,4,"He said: \"My Lord that I, the bones weakened/enfeebled from me, and the hair turned white or gray and my Lord I was not miserable/unhappy with calling you"
  19,5,"And that I, I feared the followers/dependents from behind/beyond me, and my woman (wife) was infertile to grant/present for me from at you a follower/friend"
  19,6,"(He) inherits me and (he) inherits from Jacob`s family, and my Lord make him accepted/approved/satisfied"
  19,7,"You Zacharias/Zachary , that We, We announce good news to you with a boy , his name (is) John/Yahya , We did not make for him from before (an) equivalent/equivalent in height/position"
  19,8,"He said: \"My Lord that how (could there) be for me a boy and my woman (wife) was infertile and I had reached from the old age exceeding the limit"
  19,9,"He said: \"Like that.\" Your Lord said: \"It is on Me easy/light , and I had created you from before, and you were not a thing"
  19,10,"He said: \"My Lord, make/put for me a sign/evidence.\" He said: \"Your sign/evidence (is) that you do not converse/talk (to) the people three nights straight"
  19,11,"So he emerged on (to) his nation, from the center of the assembly/the prayers` niche , so he inspired/transmitted/signaled to them that praise/glorify (at) daybreaks/early mornings and evenings/first darkness/dinnertime"
  19,12,"You John/Yahya, take The Book with power/strength, and We gave/brought him the judgment/rule (as) a boy/child/infant"
  19,13,"And compassion/kindness from at Us, and purification/correction and he was fearing and obeying"
  19,14,"And righteous/obedient with his parents, and he was not a disobedient tyrant/rebel"
  19,15,"And security/peace on him (on the) day he was born and (the) day he dies, and (the) day he be sent/resurrected/revived alive"
  19,16,And remember/mention in The Book Mary when she distantly isolated herself from her family/relation (to) an easterly/eastern place/position
  19,17,"So she took from other than them a divider/protection , so We sent to her Our Soul/Spirit , so he simulated/represented to her (as an) upright/average human"
  19,18,"She said: \"That I, I seek protection by the merciful from you, if you were fearing and obeying"
  19,19,"He said: \"Truly I am your Lord`s messenger to grant/present for you a pure/righteous boy"
  19,20,"She said: \"How/from where (there) be for me a boy and (a) human has not touched me, and I was not afornicatress/adulteress/prostitute"
  19,21,"He said: \"`Like that,` said your Lord, it is on Me easy/light , and to make/put him (as) a sign/evidence to the people, and mercy from Us, and (it was) a matter/command accomplished/ executed"
  19,22,So she was pregnant (with) him so she distantly isolated herself with him (to) a far/remote place/position
  19,23,"So the labour/childbirth came to her to (at) the palm tree`s trunk/stem, she said: \"Oh I wish I would have died before this and I was forgotten (and long) forgotten"
  19,24,"So he (Jesus) called her from below/beneath her: \"That do not be sad/grieving, your Lord had put below/beneath you a stream/clearance of a burden/generosity"
  19,25,"And shake/move to(wards) you with the palm tree`s trunk/stem, it causes freshly harvested/gathered ripe/moist (dates) to fall/drop repeatedly on you"
  19,26,"So eat and drink and be delighted/satisfied eye(s) (delight your eyes), so when you see anyone from the human, so say: `That I made a duty/vow (on myself) to the merciful, a fast , so I will not converse/speak the day/today (to) a human"
  19,27,"So she came with him (to) her nation carrying him , they said: \"You Mary, you had come (with) a strange and confusing thing"
  19,28,"You Aaron`s sister, your father was not (a) human/man of bad/evil , and your mother was not an fornicatress/adulteress/prostitute"
  19,29,"So she pointed/indicated to him, they said: \"How (do) we converse/speak (to) whom was in the crib/cradle a boy/child/infant"
  19,30,"He said: \"That I am God`s worshipper/slave, He gave/brought me The Book and He made me a prophet"
  19,31,"And He made me blessed, wherever I was/am, and He directed/commanded me with the prayers and the charity/purification as long as I continued/lasted alive"
  19,32,"And charitable/obedient with my mother, and He did not make me a miserable/unhappy tyrant/rebel"
  19,33,"And the security/peace (was) on me (on the) day I was born, and (the) day I die, and (the) day I be sent/resurrected/revived alive"
  19,34,"That (was) Jesus Mary`s son, the correct/real saying/opinion and belief which they (are) doubting/arguing in it"
  19,35,"(It) was not to God that (He) take from a child/children (son), His praise/glory, if He ordered/executed amatter/command , so but He says to it: \"Be, so it becomes"
  19,36,"And that God (is) my Lord and your Lord, so worship Him, that (is) a straight/direct road/way"
  19,37,"So the groups/parties differed/disagreed/disputed from between them, so grief/distress to those who disbelieved from an assembly of a great day"
  19,38,"Make (to) hear/listen with them, and make to see/understand , a day they come to Us, but the unjust/oppressive today (are) in evident misguidance"
  19,39,"And warn/give them notice (of) the Grief`s Day/Resurrection Day, when the matter/affair was accomplished/carried out , and they are in negligence/disregard, and they are not believing"
  19,40,"That We, We inhabit the earth/Planet Earth, and who (is) on it, and to Us they return"
  19,41,"And remember/mention in The Book Abraham, that he truly was an always very truthful prophet"
  19,42,"When he said to his father: \"You my father, for what (do) you worship what does not hear/listen, and nor see/understand , and nor enrich/suffice from you a thing"
  19,43,"You my father, that I, (it) had come to me from the knowledge, what did not come to you, so follow me, I guide you a straight/level road/way"
  19,44,"You my father, do not worship the devil, that the devil was/is to the merciful disobedient"
  19,45,"You my father, that I fear that torture touches you from the merciful, so you be to the devil an ally/follower"
  19,46,"He said: \"Are you shunning/turning away from my gods, you Abraham? If (E) you do not end/terminate/stop, I will stone you, and leave/distance me a long/life time"
  19,47,"He said: \"Security/peace on you, I will ask for forgiveness for you (from) my Lord, that He truly (was) with me generous/blessing"
  19,48,"And I separate/isolate myself from you and what you call from other than God, and I call my Lord, maybe/perhaps that I not be with my Lord`s call/prayer miserable/unhappy"
  19,49,"So when he separated/isolated himself from them, and what they call from other than God, We granted for him Issac , and Jacob and each/all, We made a prophet"
  19,50,"And We granted for them from Our mercy, and We made for them (a) truthful high and mighty/dignified tongue/language/speech"
  19,51,"And remember/mention in The Book Moses, that he truly was faithful/loyal/devoted and (he) was a messenger, a prophet"
  19,52,"And We called him from the mountain`s side/direction, the right (side), and We neared/approached him secretly conversing"
  19,53,"And We granted for him from Our mercy his brother Aaron, a prophet"
  19,54,"And remember/mention in The Book Ishmael , that he truly was truthful (in) the promise, and was a messenger, a prophet"
  19,55,"And (he) was ordering/commanding his family/people with the prayers and the charity/purification, and (he) was at his Lord accepted/approved"
  19,56,"And remember/mention in The Book Idris, that he truly was always very truthful, and a prophet"
  19,57,And We raised him a high and mighty/dignified place/position
  19,58,"Those are those who God blessed/praised on them from the prophets from Adam`s descendants; and from who We carried with Noah, , and from Abraham`s and Ishmael`s descendants, and from who We guided and We chose/purified, if the merciful`s verses/evidences are read/recited on them they fell down prostrating and weeping"
  19,59,"So succeeded/followed from after them a succession , they lost/wasted/destroyed the prayers, and they212followed the lusts/desires/cravings, so they will/shall meet/find misguidance/failure"
  19,60,"Except who repented and believed and made/did correct/righteous deeds, so those, they enter the Paradise, and they are not being caused injustice to/oppressed a thing"
  19,61,"Treed gardens/paradises (as) eternal residence which the merciful promises His worshippers/slaves with the unseen/hidden , that He truly, His promise was/is coming (E)"
  19,62,"They do not hear/listen in it nonsense/senseless talk , except (a) greeting/safety/peace and for them, (is) their provision in it (at) daybreaks/early mornings and (at) evening/first darkness/dinnertime"
  19,63,That (is) the paradise which We make inherit (to) who was fearing and obeying from Our worshippers/slaves
  19,64,"And We do not descend except with your Lord`s order/command, for Him what (is) between Our hands, and what (is) behind Us, and what (is) between that, and your Lord was not frequently forgetting"
  19,65,"The skies`/space`s and the earth`s/Planet Earth`s and what (is) between them (B)`s Lord, so worship Him, and endure patience to His worshipping, do you know (an) equivalent to Him"
  19,66,"And the human/mankind says: \"Is (it that) if I died, I will/shall (E) be brought out alive! .\"(expression of wonderment)"
  19,67,Or does not the human remember that We created him from before and (he) was not a thing
  19,68,"So by your Lord We will gather them (E), and the devils, then We will present/bring them (E) around Hell kneeling/standing on (their) toes"
  19,69,Then We will remove (E) from every group/party which of them (is) stronger arrogant/disobedience on (to) the merciful
  19,70,"Then We are (E) more knowledgeable with (about) those who, they are more worthy/deserving roasting/suffering/burning with (in) it (Hell)"
  19,71,"And that from you (there is not) except (who is) nearing/approaching it , (that) was on (by) your Lord decidedly/positively ordered/executed"
  19,72,"Then We save/rescue those who feared and obeyed, and We leave (disregard) the unjust/oppressors in it kneeling/standing on (their) toes"
  19,73,"And when Our evidences/verses evidences are read/recited on (to) them, those who disbelieved said to those who believed: \"Which (of) the two groups/parties/flocks is (in) better residence and best gathering/assembly/club"
  19,74,And how many We destroyed from before them from people of one era/generation/century? They are better home effects/money and appearance/pleasant appearance
  19,75,"Say: \"Who was in the misguidance, so the merciful will extend/spread (E) for him extension/spreading until when they saw/understood what they are being promised, either the torture, and either the Hour/Resurrection , so they will know who he is worst (in) a place/position, and weaker soldiers/warriors"
  19,76,"And God increases those who were guided (in) guidance, and the remainders the correct/righteous deeds (are) better at your Lord a replacement/compensation and better (in) a return"
  19,77,"So did you see/understand who disbelieved with Our evidences/verses, and said: \"I will be given213property/possession/wealth and children"
  19,78,"Has he seen/been informed (of) the unseen/absent , or he took/received at the merciful a promise/contract"
  19,79,"No but, We will write/dictate what he says, and We extend/spread to him from the torture extension/spreading"
  19,80,"And We make him inherit what he says, and he comes to Us singly/alone"
  19,81,"And they took/received from other than God gods, to be for them glory/might/honour"
  19,82,"No but they will disbelieve with their worshipping, and they (are) on them adversaries/opponents"
  19,83,"Do you not see/understand that We sent the devils on (to) the disbelievers, they penetrate their minds/influence them penetration of their minds/influence"
  19,84,"So do not hurry/hasten/rush on them, but We count for them counting"
  19,85,A day We gather the fearing and obeying to the merciful (as) a delegation of dignitaries
  19,86,And We drive (herd) the criminals/sinners to Hell successively in groups
  19,87,"They do not own/possess the mediation, except who took/received at the merciful a promise/contract"
  19,88,"And they said: \"The merciful took/received a child (son)"
  19,89,You had come (with) a blasphemous/disastrous thing
  19,90,"The skies/space are about to/almost split/crack/cleave from it, and the earth/Planet Earth splits/cracks open ,and the mountains fall down (in) demolition and breaking down into pieces violently with noise"
  19,91,That (E) they called to the merciful a child (son)
  19,92,And (it) would not (be) to the merciful that He takes a child (son)
  19,93,That every/each whom (is) in the skies/space and the earth/Planet Earth except is coming (E) (to) the merciful (as) a worshipper/slave
  19,94,He had counted/completed them and He counted them counting
  19,95,And all of them are coming to Him (in) the Resurrection Day singly/alone/one
  19,96,"That those who believed and made/did the correct/righteous deeds, the merciful will make/create for them love/affection"
  19,97,"So but We eased it with your tongue/language, to announce good news with it (to) the fearing and obeying, and warn/give notice with it (to) a nation (in) harsh/violent dispute"
  19,98,"And how many before them We destroyed from people of one era/generation/century, do you sense/feel from them from anyone, or hear for them (a) low voice/whisper/faint sound"